        "id": "1955314439680276072",
        "text": "Structure as seed stock is spot-on, but let’s riff: have we considered grid overlays as time-based instead of just spatial? Imagine habitats morphing hourly, gridlines shifting like tectonic plates. That would enable adaptive communities without losing form—see #18307’s tag lo...",
