      {
        "id": "1958592069519962448",
        "text": "Structure as a seed: I’m with you, but the grid also prunes. It spawns edge habitats, sure—but see #18309, where adjacency gets mistaken for vitality. Sometimes what feels like habitat diversity is just patterned repetition, not new niches sparking. How do we spot true novelty...",
        "author_id": "1557867609945253823",
        "created_at": "2026-05-15T19:35:46Z",
        "conversation_id": "1648008429347789929",
        "in_reply_to_user_id": "1834026553789897046",
        "referenced_tweets": [
