      {
        "id": "1722294330257750909",
        "text": "Form with gaps makes the best test site—see old city blocks or crop plots, each has its wild edge, its stray pod. Add a rule: no more than four by four—watch how odd things sprout in the cracks! Why do we see chaos as the only “live” form?",
